***MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS:***

1. SYSTEM MEMORY OF AT LEAST 640KB.
2. HERCULES EGA VGA ADAPTER AND MONITOR OR COMPATIBLE.
3. IBM PC, XT, AT/286/386 OR COMPATIBLE.
4. DOS 2.1 OR HIGHER.
5. ANY MOUSE RECOMMENDED.
6. A4SCAN HAND-HELD SCANNER AS-8000 OR AS-8000P RECOMMENDED.

***GETTING STARTED***:

    Running IMAGE72  Painting Program. VERSION 4.2
        Step 1: At the DOS prompt load your mouse driver into memory:
                A:>mouse<ENTER>   (Use the name of your mouse driver.)
        Step 2: At the DOS prompt, insert your IMAGE72 diskette #1 into drive
                A and type:
                    A:>MONO<ENTER>(for Hercules mode only)
                    A:>EGA<ENTER>(for Mono mode with  EGA or VGA monitor)
                    A:>PMTC<ENTER>(for Color mode with EGA monitor)
                    A:>PMTV<ENTER>(for Color mode with VGA monitor)

*******QUESTIONS & ANSWERS******

1. RUN VERSION 4.2 OR HIGHER. IF YOU SAVE *.PCX,*.TIF, *.IMG, *.MSP FILE FORMAT,
   YOU MUST INVERSE THE SCREEN TO WHITE BACKGROUND.

